main event: Radar operators at R.C.A.F. Station Trenton observed an unidentified airborne object over Lake Ontario on December 6, 1965.
interesting points: The object was tracked for approximately 5 minutes and traveled a distance of 50 miles,The object was described as a strong, fast-moving target by both radar operator and air traffic controller,No other aircraft were reported in the vicinity during the sighting,Weather conditions were favorable with visibility of 10-15 miles,Two photos were included with the report, although they do not contain identifiable objects.
witness description: RADAR OPERATOR JOHN FORJOE and AIR TRAFFIC CONTROLLER ARTHUR TURNER
